<section class="explainer">
  <p>
    Each quarter, one stock gets picked and held — in principle, for 25 years. The same fixed
    dollar amount goes into the pick and into the S&amp;P 500 Total Return index on the same date,
    so the comparison is clean. No rebalancing means each position is held at its original lot
    size. Returns include dividends reinvested. The math is straightforward and the methodology
    is fixed.
  </p>
  <p>
    The short list — the four stocks that made serious consideration each quarter — goes to
    subscribers. The pick is always public.
  </p>
</section>

<style>
  .explainer {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: var(--surface);
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
  }
  .explainer p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .explainer p + p {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }
</style>
